==Changes==
{{Subject changes header}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 28 April 2016
|update = Calling Pets & Deadman Death
|poll = Old School Content Poll 41: Bank placeholders & Skillcapes
|change = It is now possible to add compost or supercompost to any farming patch during any growth stage of a crop.
}}
{{subject changes
|date = 8 October 2015
|update = Smoke Battlestaff Buff
|change = Left-click pruning farming patches now checks for held magic secateurs.
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 28 May 2015
|update = Farming & World Switcher Tweaks
|change = The tool leprechaun at the farming patch just south of Falador has been moved slightly to be closer to where players are when using the farming patch.
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 16 April 2015
|update = Clan Wars Game Modes & More
|change = Farmers will no longer protect Poison Ivy bushes, as they are immune to disease.
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 5 March 2015
|update = Achievement Diaries
|poll = Old School Achievement Diary Rewards Poll
|change =
{{*}} You now receive 10% more experience from the Falador [[farming patch]] if you have completed the [[Falador Medium Diary]].<br/><br/>
{{*}} The [[tree patch]] in [[Falador]] will no longer become [[diseased]] if you have completed the [[Falador Elite Diary]].<br/><br/>
{{*}} You now receive increased yields from the [[Catherby]] [[herb patch]] for the completion of [[Kandarin Diary|Kandarin Diaries]]:

*5% more for the [[Kandarin Medium|medium diary]].
*10% more for the [[Kandarin Hard Diary|hard diary]].
*15% more for the [[Kandarin Elite|elite diary]].
}}
{{Subject changes
|date = 18 September 2014
|update = Bounty Hunter
|poll = Old School feature poll - Content Poll 24
|change = The cactus patch found in Al-Kharid now has an accompanying NPC to protect your cactus for the small cost of 6 cadava berries.
}}
